@dpkp should we file a separate issue for what @ikatson is describing? We can reproduce the issue. We have 4 good kafka brokers, and 1 bad one (the first one). kafka-python crashes because it can't connect to the first one.

Though another kafka client (in go), https://github.com/Shopify/sarama can talk to the kafka VIP and successfully connects to other brokers and routes around the bad one. (It actually connect to all of them regardless).

It seems like kafka-python relies on the first broker being good, or it crashes. The client should be more resilient.

