I have a proposal like this:

```
{
    // attributes defined on global level
    "outer_padding": 1,
    "spaces": 1,
    // use a unified "lines" attribute that includes all lines 
    // instead of "above" attribute that doesn't contain the last line
    "lines": [
        {
            // line specific attributes that override global attributes
            "outer_padding": 2,
            "spaces": 2,
            "left": [
                ...
            ],
            "right": [
                ...
            ]
        },
        {
            "left": [
                ...
            ],
            "right": [
                ...
            ]
        },
        {
            "outer_padding": 0,
            "spaces": 1,
            "left": [
                {
                    // per-segment attributes that override line specific ones
                    "dividers": {
                        "left": {
                            // comparing to "draw_hard_divider": false,
                            // this brings more freedom for setting segment specific dividers
                            "hard": "",           
                            "soft": ""
                        }
                    },
                    // segment specific "outer_padding" will take effect only if
                    // it is the first segment in the line
                    "outer_padding": 0,
                    "spaces": 1,
                    "type": "string",
                    "contents": "▸",
                    "highlight_groups": ["background"]
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}
```

In this way, attributes like "outer_padding", "spaces", or even "dividers" can be specified on a multi-level basis. This will allow users to define line specific behaviors and even segment specific behaviors, which cannot be done currently.

