@danielballan  You're right, we should keep the `minmass_version_change`. I now figured out what changed in this PR so that the original tests broke. Because of a reduced (and square! see #361) boxcar kernel, features are dimmer after the bandpassing, leading to lower `mass` values.

This makes sense: a rolling average with a smaller kernel is less smoothed out than one with a larger kernel.  If you subtract this from the original image, the smaller the kernel, the dimmer the features. I explained this in the docstring of the new `minmass_v04_change`.

Counterintuitively, the locate precision increased in this PR: `ep` is now always larger than the real precision (see last commit to `test_ep`). One reason for this is described in #401. I now added an explicit test for this. `ep` can be seen as an upper boundary to the precision.

